org.azyva.dragom.model.plugin

Interface RemoteBuilderPlugin.RemoteBuildHandle

  • Enclosing interface:
    RemoteBuilderPlugin

    public static interface RemoteBuilderPlugin.RemoteBuildHandle
    Represents a remote build and allows obtaining its status and interacting with it.

    • Method Detail

      • getModuleVersion

        ModuleVersion getModuleVersion()
        Returns:
        ModuleVersion associated with the remote build.

      • getLocation

        String getLocation()
        Returns:
        Human-readable description of the location where the remote build executes. For example, this can include the URL of a job build in Jenkins.

      • getRemoteBuildStatus

        RemoteBuilderPlugin.RemoteBuildHandle.RemoteBuildStatus getRemoteBuildStatus()
        Returns the RemoteBuilderPlugin.RemoteBuildHandle.RemoteBuildStatus.

        If the last known status of the build is such that it can change, this method should query the remote build system for the new status.

        However, if the last known status of the build is RemoteBuilderPlugin.RemoteBuildHandle.RemoteBuildStatus.CANNOT_BUILD_REMOTELY or RemoteBuilderPlugin.RemoteBuildHandle.RemoteBuildStatus.COMPLETED, it is expected to be returned immediately without wasting time querying the remote build system.

        Returns:
        RemoteBuildStatus.

      • getCannotBuildRemotelyReason

        String getCannotBuildRemotelyReason()
        Returns the reason why the build cannot be performed remotely.

        Can only be called if getRemoteBuildStatus returned RemoteBuildStatus.CANNOT_BUILD_REMOTELY.

        Returns:
        See description.

      • waitCompleted

        void waitCompleted()
        Blocks until the remote build is completed.

      • isSuccess

        boolean isSuccess()
        Indicates the build was successful, as opposed to a failure.

        If the build is not completed, this method blocks until it is.

        Returns:
        Indicates the build was successful.

      • getLog

        void getLog(Writer writerLog)
        Writes the log of the build in the provided Writer.

        If the build is not completed, this method blocks until it is.

        Parameters:
        writerLog - Writer.
